  "notes": "Libyan Arabic. Two main varieties: Western (Tripoli): Maghrebi features, θ → /t/; Eastern (Benghazi/Barqa): more conservative, θ preserved, Egyptian-influenced features. ق → /q/ PRESERVED in most Libyan varieties (conservative). Vowel reduction less extreme than Moroccan. Italian colonial influence (1911–1943): /p/ in loans, some /tʃ/.",
